<span id="freeTextContainer8951680033265248401">I found it difficult to read this book at first. The author&apos;s story is so raw and painful, especially his childhood, that I barely got through it. Even as he grows into a youth, his struggle to survive remains as bleak and difficult as ever as he relates a truly Darwinian or &quot;survival of the fittest&quot; existence. Illiterate, dirt poor, desperate, and hopeless, his story takes a dramatic turn when he ends up in prison. I know his real-life story eventually has a happy ending but the journey there, </span>
  <span id="freeText8951680033265248401" style="display:none">I found it difficult to read this book at first. The author's story is so raw and painful, especially his childhood, that I barely got through it. Even as he grows into a youth, his struggle to survive remains as bleak and difficult as ever as he relates a truly Darwinian or "survival of the fittest" existence. Illiterate, dirt poor, desperate, and hopeless, his story takes a dramatic turn when he ends up in prison. I know his real-life story eventually has a happy ending but the journey there, at least in this book, was exhausting! </span>
  <a data-text-id="8951680033265248401" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
