<div id="review_3875886538" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3875886538" />
    <a title="Jeeshan Shams Choudhury" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/128169837-jeeshan-shams-choudhury"><img alt="Jeeshan Shams Choudhury" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610281353p2/128169837.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3875886538?book_show_action=true">Apr 10, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeeshan Shams Choudhury" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeeshan Shams Choudhury" href="/user/show/128169837-jeeshan-shams-choudhury">Jeeshan Shams Choudhury</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781846590108" href="/book/show/155766.For_Bread_Alone">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3875886538" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13000671198387330038">A harrowing autobiographical tale of a young man’s upbringing in colonial Morocco, <i>For Bread Alone </i> details Mohamed Choukri’s struggle to survive and find purpose in a society ravaged by poverty, violence and alienation. <br/><br/>The straightforward yet descriptive style of writing used for this memoir produces highly personal moments of almost unfathomable tragedy, but amid this bleakness and depravity also shines an endearing honesty within the protagonist, whose desire to overcome his circumstances an</span>
  <span id="freeText13000671198387330038" style="display:none">A harrowing autobiographical tale of a young man’s upbringing in colonial Morocco, <i>For Bread Alone </i> details Mohamed Choukri’s struggle to survive and find purpose in a society ravaged by poverty, violence and alienation. <br /><br />The straightforward yet descriptive style of writing used for this memoir produces highly personal moments of almost unfathomable tragedy, but amid this bleakness and depravity also shines an endearing honesty within the protagonist, whose desire to overcome his circumstances and find security culminates in his ultimate personal liberation, by gaining the ability to read and write as a young adult.<br /><br />Whilst there could therefore be a tendency to see this book’s message as one of celebration and human progress because of Choukri’s journey to literacy, I believe that the following quote by the author himself provides the best insight into the purpose of sharing his early life story with the world:<br /><br /><i>“I saw that writing could also be a way to expose, to protest against those who have stolen my childhood, my teenage hood and a piece of my youthfulness. At that moment, my writing became committed.”</i><br /><br />As a work of protest and reminder of the injustices created by poverty and colonialism, <i>For Bread Alone </i> is well worth reading.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13000671198387330038" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

