<div id="review_2622756538" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2622756538" />
    <a title="Clifton" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1930905-clifton"><img alt="Clifton" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1326515814p2/1930905.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2622756538?book_show_action=true">Dec 10, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Clifton" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Clifton" href="/user/show/1930905-clifton">Clifton</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/22397836-for-bread-alone">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2622756538" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8240616155082305344">Paul Bowles, translator of Mohamed Choukri’s autobiographical novel, For Bread Alone, writes in his Introduction to the book, “It has been my experience that the illiterate, not having learned to classify what goes into his memory, rememberers everything.” He finds in the case of Choukri this truth has been of great advantage for the author writing his own story as fiction. <br/><br/>When I wrote my own autobiographical novel, Wrestling With Angels: A Tale of Two Brothers, I had no such an advantage. I di</span>
  <span id="freeText8240616155082305344" style="display:none">Paul Bowles, translator of Mohamed Choukri’s autobiographical novel, For Bread Alone, writes in his Introduction to the book, “It has been my experience that the illiterate, not having learned to classify what goes into his memory, rememberers everything.” He finds in the case of Choukri this truth has been of great advantage for the author writing his own story as fiction. <br /><br />When I wrote my own autobiographical novel, Wrestling With Angels: A Tale of Two Brothers, I had no such an advantage. I did, however, have the advantage of diaries and journals I’d kept since I was 10. Choukri moves seamlessly through one of the most extremely violent, drug and alcohol filled deprived childhoods in fiction, without self censoring and without sensationalism.<br /><br />A bildungsroman, For Bread Alone is an extraordinary story, a cultural lesson as it were for non-Muslim and non-Moroccan readers. That this intelligent, imaginative boy should choose to better himself is in itself extraordinary, considering the many who do not. Without revealing the end, I can say For Bread Alone is a blazing testiment to the human determination and ability to not only survive but to make and create something extremely important and lasting. I can’t recommend For Bread Alone too highly.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8240616155082305344" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


